title: Grateful Dead Live at Rainbow Theater on 1981-10-06
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street-> Minglewood Blues-> It Must Have Been The Roses, Little Red Rooster, Althea, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Good Time Blues, Cumberland Blues-> Looks Like Rain-> Might As Well

Set 2

Women Are Smarter, High Time, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Blues For Allah Jam-> The Wheel-> Sugar Magnolia-> Stella Blue-> Good Lovin', E:Sunshine Daydream-> E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
love these sandwiches see also

https://archive.org/details/gd1981-10-13.sbd.128542.MrBill.flac16

this one must be unique. 4 stars for that alone.

too bad Jer blows the peak Stella lyric, but then he lets his guitar sing !

Bobby’s ‘promise’ 
“If you’re good, and we’re good, maybe we’ll see you again, soon ...” or words to that effect.
(Bobby, at the end of Brokedown Palace)

We had to wait soooo long ...

I have a first generation tape of this concert, from the friend who foxed the Rainbow’s security and managed to keep taping.

It was bliss ... too many standouts to mention. 
All four dates were great, but this one, and 4/10/81, were stellar.

And Jerry’s voice could break as many times as it wanted, I’d still rather listen to him than to anyone else .... and yes, his guitar was singing so sweetly ....
